intro_nightmare:
    clear_dialog
    stop music
    run transition generic_black
    wait 4000
    "The day comes to a close, and there is naught left to do but retreat to your chrysalis."
    clear_dialog
    "It is there, in the cloying embrace of sleep, that you find yourself somewhere new."
    clear_dialog
    play ambient welcomeToEngland-CUNT 1
    "The floor is a dirtied, cracked ceramic. Dark strands of hair curl about the bottom of the wide pit you have found yourself in like great serpents. A foot or so in front of you is an even deeper, darker pit rimmed with rusted metal."
    "Above you is darkness, save light reflected off some great mirror that illuminates your prison with pale moonlight."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "If not for a faint buzzing somewhere <span class='nightmare'>above</span> it would be silent."
        "Hello?":
            run transition_nightmare intro_ghost
            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Hello? Hello. Hello...</span>"
            choice:
                "There is no response, save your own echo. You are so alone. Perhaps you always have been?"
                "Orb? Lovely Lady? Nasty Girl? Is anyone there?":
                    talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Is anyone there? Anyone there. Anyone there...</span>"
                    clear_dialog
                    "Your scratchy, *deep* little voice bounces off of the walls, worms its way back into your ears, and echoes like a gong, deep inside your mind fuzz."
                    "Your voice always rings in your mind fuzz."
                    "It's the worst sound in the world, and you have to listen to it forever."
    clear_dialog
    play sound nkvd
    choice:
        talk nightmare talk "Goodnight <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>, I don't think we've formally met."
        "Who are you!?":
            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>You!? You. You...</span>"
        "Where's Orb!? Where's Lovely Lady!? Where's Nasty Girl!?":
            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Cube!? Man. boy...</span>"
            play sound nkvd
            choice:
                talk nightmare talk "So accusatory! They're sleeping soundly, <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>. Isn't that what normal mammals do at night, instead of wandering about their own little ceramic wasteland shouting at themselves?"
                "Who are you!?":
                    talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>You!? You. You...</span>"
    play sound nkvd
    talk nightmare talk "Me? Oh <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>, you silly thing, I'm your best friend. I'm the thing that makes you *you*. I am your *life*."
    clear_dialog
    play sound nkvd
    choice:
        talk nightmare talk "You and your wellbeing matter to me, <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>. Even if I clearly don't at all matter to you, seeing as you went and *forgot* me."
        "I forgot you?":
            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Myself? Myself. Myself...</span>"
            play sound nkvd
            choice:
                talk nightmare talk "You did! Would you like to get reacquainted?"
                "I suppose.":
                    talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Suppose. Suppose. suppose...</span>"
                    play sound nkvd
                    talk nightmare talk "That makes me so happy, <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span. Thank you."
                "I'd prefer not to, you seem a bit scary.":
                    talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Scary. Scary. scary...</span>"
                    play sound nkvd
                    talk nightmare talk "Scary? Me? No, not at all. We're friends. We're <span class='nightmare'>friends</span>. Besides, you *want* to remember."
    clear_dialog
    play sound nkvd
    choice:
        talk nightmare talk "Take a look around, <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>, does anything in this funny little place catch your eye? Anything at all?"
        "[Look around]":
            choice:
                "There's nothing you haven't already seen. Parched, cracked ceramic, sodden, greasy hairs, a pit that falls away into nothing."
                "There's nothing to see!":
                    talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Nothing to see! To see. To see...</span>"
    play sound nkvd
    talk nightmare talk "You haven't noticed <span class='nightmare'>it</span>? Come on <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>, you can do it, look around. It's not like there's anything else here to look at, hmm?"
    play sound nkvd
    talk nightmare talk "I think one of your hairs is over there, about a meter thick, but what are you going to do with that? Gnaw on it? No, of course not."
    clear_dialog
    play sound nkvd
    choice:
        talk nightmare talk "Use your eyes. There's <span class='nightmare'>*something*</span> up *there*. Teetering precariously on the brink of the basin so *very* high up. Do you see <span class='nightmare'>it</span>? A feather in the right place would send <span class='nightmare'>it</span> tumbling. Falling. <span class='nightmare'>Sliding down to meet you.</span>"
        "[Look to the brink]":
            clear_dialog
            play ambient welcomeToEngland-CUNT_two 2
            run transition_nightmare nightmare_one
            choice:
                "The Nightmare is correct. There's <span class='nightmare'>*something*</span> up there. A glimmer of reflected moonlight reveals to you the colour of your own eye, but pale. So so pale."
                "W- what is <span class='nightmare'>it</span>?":
                    talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>It? It. It...</span>"
                    play sound nkvd
                    choice:
                        talk nightmare talk "Why don't you take a closer look?"
                        "<span class='nightmare'>It</span>'s far away, I can't reach <span class='nightmare'>it</span>...":
                            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>It. It. It...</span>"
                            play sound nkvd
                            choice:
                                talk nightmare talk "This little dream belongs to you, <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>. You can *make* <span class='nightmare'>it</span> fall. <span class='nightmare'>Make it slide down to meet you.</span>"
                                "[Make the thing fall. <span class='nightmare'>Make it slide down to meet you</span>]":
                                    jump intro_nightmare_fall
                                "I don't want to!":
                                    talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>I don't want to! Don't want to. Don't want to...</span>"
                                    play sound nkvd
                                    talk nightmare talk "Then let me help you. That's what friends are for, isn't it?"
                                    jump intro_nightmare_fall
                        "I don't want to!":
                            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>I don't want to! Don't want to. Don't want to...</span>"
                            play sound nkvd
                            talk nightmare talk "Then let me help you. That's what friends are for :-)"
                            jump intro_nightmare_fall
                        "I'd like to wake up now.":
                            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Now. Now. Now...</span>"
                            play sound nkvd
                            talk nightmare talk "Not yet, <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>, we need to do this, okay? It's for your own good. Tell you what though, since you seem nervous, I'll help you. That's what friends are for :-)"
                            jump intro_nightmare_fall

intro_nightmare_fall:
    clear_dialog
    play sound scrape
    "<span class='nightmare'>The thing slides down the side of the basin.</span>"
    "<span class='nightmare'>Its</span> fingernails screech against the cracked, rough ceramic. A painful, high-pitched sound. <span class='nightmare'>It</span> leaves a streak of thick black liquid in <span class='nightmare'>its</span> wake."
    clear_dialog
    play ambient welcomeToEngland-CUNT_three 3
    run transition_nightmare nightmare_two
    "<span class='nightmare'>It</span> hits the basin with a thud. The sound of a bone crunching. <span class='nightmare'>It</span> does not stop. No, <span class='nightmare'>it</span> continues moving towards you with <span class='nightmare'>its</span> own inertia, as if wanting to be with you. To touch you. To smother you. To clamber on top of you and melt into you. To go *inside* you."
    "<span class='nightmare'>It</span> bumps into your feet, one hand hangs limply down the metal rimmed pit aside you."
    clear_dialog
    "The <span class='nightmare'>thing</span> is <span class='nightmare'>you</span>. <span class='nightmare'>Its</span> fur is more akin to scouring wire, <span class='nightmare'>its</span> face more angular, <span class='nightmare'>its</span> eyes colder, but <span class='nightmare'>it</span> *is* <span class='nightmare'>you</span>. <span class='nightmare'>It</span> *was* <span class='nightmare'>you.</span> You were <span class='nightmare'>it.</span>"
    clear_dialog
    "The flies infesting the corpse's eyes cause them to twitch just enough to give it a facsimile of life. <span class='nightmare'>It</span> crawls with the kind of bugs that seem to appear spontaneously around a corpse, the kind you never see anywhere else."
    "A worm, long, endless, curls its way through the <span class='nightmare'>thing's</span> bulk. Sometimes internally, sometimes externally. A trickle of ink black sludge leaks from the corner of the <span class='nightmare'>thing's</span> maw and pools around <span class='nightmare'>its</span> head."
    "Pale worms, translucent even, if not for the *stuff* inside their digestive tract, writhe inside of the <span class='nightmare'>it</span>."
    clear_dialog
    "The <span class='nightmare'>thing</span> before you is no mammal."
    "<span class='nightmare'>It</span> is a <span class='nightmare'>monster</span>. <span class='nightmare'>It</span> is <span class='nightmare'>you</span>. <span class='nightmare'>It</span> was <span class='nightmare'>you. And <span class='nightmare'>it</span> could be you again.</span>"
    clear_dialog
    play sound nkvd
    talk nightmare talk "There's the cliche isn't there? The one you see in creatively inept newspaper comic strips and theatre productions, the cliche of someone masking their pain, their terror, with a smiling visard. You don't need to do that though, do you <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>?"
    play sound nkvd
    talk nightmare talk "Your sharp little face already dons a smiling little mask, but it's a facade, that's all. Your bones creak under it, as if they might escape."
    clear_dialog
    play sound nkvd
    choice:
        talk nightmare talk "There is no hiding from your *true* face. <span class='nightmare'>It</span> will always be there, one layer of epidermis below the surface, staring back at you in the bathroom mirror, *forever*. Everyone else can see <span class='nightmare'>it</span>, <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>. Everyone else can see <span class='nightmare'>the thing on the floor.</span>"
        "That... that <span class='nightmare'>thing</span> on the floor is *me*?":
            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Me? Me. Me...</span>"
    play sound nkvd
    choice:
        talk nightmare talk "No <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>, that <span class='nightmare'>thing</span> on the floor is <span class='nightmare'>me</span>."
        "But you just said <span class='nightmare'>it</span> was me!":
            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>You! You. You...</span>"
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The <span class='nightmare'>thing</span> on the floor of the basin twitches. It's not the kind of twitch a dying animal makes, it's the kind of twitch a corpse that has turned into a *home* for an animal makes."           
        "I want to wake up! I want to wake up I want to go back to how I was! To forget all this!":
            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Was! Was. Was...</span>"
            play sound nkvd
            talk nightmare talk "You *are* going back to how you were, <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>. There is a serenity to oblivion, yes. I'm sure today has been quite the change for you."
            clear_dialog
            play sound nkvd
            choice:
                talk nightmare talk "Your existence is a howling maelstrom of brutality, and for a moment you found yourself in the eye. The place where the terrors swirl around, but are out of reach, but it's time, <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>. It's time to step back into the tempest."
                "I want to scream! I want to cry!":
                    talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Scream! Cry! Scream. Cry. Scream... Cry...</span>"
                    play sound nkvd
                    choice:
                        talk nightmare talk "You're sound asleep right now, but if it pleases you, why not have a cry?"
                        "[Scream. Cry]":
                            play sound nkvd
                            choice:
                                talk nightmare talk "Do you know *why* we're discussing this, Ghost?"
                                "I don't really know anything, I'm dumb as shit...":
                                    play sound nkvd
                                    talk nightmare talk "Then let me enlighten you."
    clear_dialog
    play sound nkvd
    talk nightmare talk "You aren't on HRT at the moment. You ran out of your grey market goods a few days ago, and now you need to go beg a doctor for some."
    play sound nkvd
    talk nightmare talk "You're full of it. Testosterone. It's poison, pumping through your veins, making you right. <span class='nightmare'>Fixing you.</span> Putting you back the way you are supposed to be."
    clear_dialog
    play sound nkvd
    talk nightmare talk "I'd have reminded you sooner, but oestradiol therapy is kind of cheating, right? So I thought it fair to give testosterone a head start."
    play sound nkvd
    talk nightmare talk "Let's see who can win the race, or rather, win your *face*; the dainty, nimble little fingertips of oestradiol or the permanently disfiguring effects of testosterone!"
    play sound nkvd
    choice:
        talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>Ready... set... GO!</span>"
        "Fuck FUCK FUCK.":
            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Fuck. Fuck. Fuck...</span>"
        "It's not poison, it's just not for me. You're being incredibly insensitive right now...":
            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Now. Now. Now...</span>"
            play sound nkvd
            choice:
                talk nightmare talk "It *is* poison. It's poison and it's <span class='nightmare'>going to fucking kill you.</span>"
                "Fuck! You're right! Fuck! Fuck fuck fuck fuck!":
                    talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Fuck! Fuck. Fuck...</span>"
    clear_dialog
    play sound nkvd
    talk nightmare talk "I don't know why you're so bothered really, when the Greater War breaks out Anglia's oestradiol supplies won't last long without imports from Oceania. You'll be all back to normal, and even sadder for what you've lost."
    play sound nkvd
    choice:
        talk nightmare talk "Why set yourself up for heartbreak, hmm?"
        "Just tell me where to get hormones...":
            talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Hormones. Hormones. Hormones...</span>"
            play sound nkvd
            talk nightmare talk "Fine. If that's truly what you want..."
            clear_dialog
            play sound nkvd
            choice:
                talk nightmare talk "You will find them far beyond the Gates of Venus, a gate through which only those of staunchest courage may pass..."
                "That seems needlessly difficult...":
                    talk ghost talk "<span class='nightmare'>Difficult. Difficult. Difficult...</span>"
                    play sound nkvd
                    talk nightmare talk "Oh yes. It is. The Keeper of the Gate, and the... the <span class='nightmare'>*thing*</span> that lies beyond it want only one thing, <span class='writtenText'>'Ghost'</span>."
                    clear_dialog
                    play sound nkvd
                    talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>They want to kill you.</span>"
                    add_level nightmare 5
                    stop ambient 1
                    stop ambient 2
                    stop ambient 3
                    jump dream_main